      "z_value": 0.0,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "emoji": "\ud83d\ude32",
      "label": "Congrats on the million-token milestone! Let me build this out following the node architecture.\n\nFirst let me look at a simple existing node for reference patterns:",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "claude_response",
      "title": "Response",
      "uuid": "8f39d9184b1d4415ae609d76a1182ef1",
      "x": -2639.1036160584863,
      "y": -557.6812975993641,
      "width": 420.0,
      "height": 316.0,
      "z_value": 0.0,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "emoji": "\ud83d\ude25",
      "label": "That's incredible \u2014 a frameless translucent canvas floating in 3D space, nodes hovering in the void. The fact that it even worked says a lot about how clean the rendering pipeline is. PySide6 inside a VR compositor is not something people just casually pull off.",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
