    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "claude_response",
      "title": "Response",
      "uuid": "e8754270dbd94d68a4b48301a62c2417",
      "x": -999999.0,
      "y": -999999.0,
      "width": 420.0,
      "height": 316.0,
      "z_value": 0.0,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "emoji": "\ud83d\ude17",
      "label": "Good \u2014 `source_path` is the right persistent identifier. Now I need to:\n\n1. Save `preview_pinned` and `preview_pinned_path` when pin state changes\n2. On session load, find the matching `ImageNode` and restore the pin",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "claude_response",
      "title": "Response",
      "uuid": "21fd556d31f848c8babad4e94e0287c5",
      "x": -999999.0,
      "y": -999999.0,
      "width": 420.0,
      "height": 288.0,
      "z_value": 0.0,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "emoji": "\ud83d\ude2f",
      "label": "Clear picture. I'll:\n1. Save `preview_pinned` + `preview_pinned_path` when pin toggles\n2. Add `_restore_pinned_preview()` called after session loads (deferred so nodes are in the scene)\n3. Clear the saved pin when unpinning",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "claude_response",
      "title": "Response",
      "uuid": "2e1b0e7f94664341bcb50438ea52601e",
      "x": -999999.0,
      "y": -999999.0,
      "width": 420.0,
      "height": 176.0,
      "z_value": 0.0,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "emoji": "\ud83d\ude0b",
      "label": "Now track `_pinned_source_path` when the preview updates, and add the restore method:",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "claude_response",
      "title": "Response",
      "uuid": "cf75853c406347089b1e57e3c8d00dbb",
      "x": -999999.0,
      "y": -999999.0,
      "width": 420.0,
      "height": 176.0,
      "z_value": 0.0,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "emoji": "\ud83e\udd70",
      "label": "Now update `_on_selection_changed` to record the source path whenever a new image lands in the preview:",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "claude_response",
      "title": "Response",
      "uuid": "b8093edd8bb847378cacf39e5d85e881",
      "x": -999999.0,
      "y": -999999.0,
      "width": 420.0,
      "height": 148.0,
      "z_value": 0.0,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "emoji": "\ud83d\ude18",
      "label": "Now call `_restore_pinned_preview` after the session loads:",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
      "title": "proxy pixmap",
      "uuid": "dec94e4945984c97acb06f405dc4df05",
      "x": -756.0,
      "y": -1164.0,
      "width": 157.40086609892387,
      "height": 60.21130695229317,
      "z_value": 0.0,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "emoji": "\ud83d\ude0e",
      "label": "proxy pixmap",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
      "title": "Vision metadata",
      "uuid": "d2270a6e44b9408d9db16b3289943984",
      "x": -809.0,
      "y": -1317.0,
      "width": 186.94340738282068,
      "height": 65.28002818652635,
      "z_value": 0.0,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "emoji": "\ud83d\ude0e",
      "label": "Vision metadata",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "claude_response",
      "title": "Response",
      "uuid": "709f72ee0fee4d32b84e93c33db397db",
      "x": -999999.0,
      "y": -999999.0,
      "width": 420.0,
      "height": 596.0,
      "z_value": 0.0,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "emoji": "\ud83e\uddf8",
      "label": "Done. What persists across restarts:\n\n- `ui.preview_pinned = true/false` \u2014 whether the panel is pinned\n- `ui.preview_pinned_path = \"/abs/path/to/image.jpg\"` \u2014 which image was pinned, matched by `source_path`\n\nOn startup, after the session loads, `_restore_pinned_preview` walks the scene, finds the `ImageNode` with the matching path, loads its pixmap into the panel, and silently re-engages the pin button (via `blockSignals` so it doesn't re-trigger the save unnecessarily). If the image node is no longer on the canvas the pin simply doesn't restore.",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
      "title": "Aboutnode's colors",
      "uuid": "a6c4a8aa22104dd59d6546d83d8d64e7",
      "x": -996.0,
      "y": -1245.0,
      "width": 218.20777963751766,
      "height": 58.0526375081713,
      "z_value": 0.0,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "emoji": "\ud83d\ude25",
      "label": "Aboutnode's colors",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "claude_response",
      "title": "Response",
      "uuid": "bb22916f68914b20aeb80bed5a25fab9",
      "x": -999999.0,
      "y": -999999.0,
      "width": 420.0,
      "height": 176.0,
      "z_value": 0.0,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "emoji": "\ud83d\ude0e",
      "label": "Let me read the current state of the function to see what actually got written:",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "claude_response",
      "title": "Response",
      "uuid": "553a238b598044dc82bd28efd9b699d4",
      "x": -999999.0,
      "y": -999999.0,
      "width": 420.0,
      "height": 316.0,
      "z_value": 0.0,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "emoji": "\ud83d\ude25",
      "label": "Found it. `NW` and `NH` are floats from `rect().width()/height()`, so `max(NW, NH) // 2` is also a float \u2014 and `range()` rejects float arguments with a `TypeError`, which swallows the whole spawn silently. The node was being created at -999,999 and abandoned there.",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "claude_response",
      "title": "Response",
      "uuid": "7fdec9139eb64df2ac93708b0e6e7c23",
      "x": -999999.0,
      "y": -999999.0,
      "width": 420.0,
      "height": 204.0,
      "z_value": 0.0,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "emoji": "\ud83d\ude09",
      "label": "`int()` first, then `// 2`, plus a `max(1, ...)` guard so it can't be zero on a degenerate node. The spiral search will now run correctly.",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "claude_response",
      "title": "Response",
      "uuid": "654d8caf0a21459fb54a0a797cd66035",
      "x": -999999.0,
      "y": -999999.0,
      "width": 420.0,
      "height": 428.0,
      "z_value": 0.0,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "emoji": "\ud83d\ude2e",
      "label": "The bug is in `_clear`. `QGraphicsItem` itself has a `data(key)` method, so `hasattr(item, 'data')` is `True` for **every** item in the scene \u2014 including Port ellipses, which also have `rect()` from `QGraphicsEllipseItem`. Every probe hits a port and returns `False`, so nothing ever spawns.\n\nFix: check `isinstance` against `BaseNode` instead:",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "claude_response",
      "title": "Response",
      "uuid": "3df3a6200355419a8958f37cce45bee2",
      "x": -999999.0,
      "y": -999999.0,
      "width": 420.0,
      "height": 372.0,
      "z_value": 0.0,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "emoji": "\ud83e\udd70",
      "label": "The root cause: `QGraphicsItem.data(key)` is a Qt method that exists on every graphics item, so `hasattr(item, 'data')` was `True` for ports, wires, everything \u2014 and `QGraphicsEllipseItem` (which ports extend) also has `rect()`. Every probe hit a port and blocked. `isinstance(item, BaseNode)` only matches actual canvas nodes.",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "image",
      "title": "Image",
      "uuid": "661d67f5648d4b3ead75e57393082439",
      "x": 1333.0,
      "y": 150.67161204180888,
      "width": 533.5794799995263,
      "height": 524.1526421376257,
      "z_value": 0.0,
      "ports_visible": false,
